transcode_audio

public static final Configuration.Config transcode_audio
Transcode the audio or just copy it.
The default is true.

skip_transcoded_audio_format_check

public static final Configuration.Config skip_transcoded_audio_format_check
If the transcoded audio format check is skipped the program only checks if the file exists, not its format. Checking each file format takes a while on large data sets and is only needed if the transcoded audio file format is changed.
The default is true.

transcoded_audio_sampling_rate

public static final Configuration.Config transcoded_audio_sampling_rate
The sampling rate for the transcoded audio.
The default rate is 44.1 kHz.

transcoded_audio_codec

public static final Configuration.Config transcoded_audio_codec
The audio codec used for the transcoded files.
The default is pcm_s16le: signed 16 bit little endian PCM.
See The JAVE (Java Audio Video Encoder) library web site.

transcoded_audio_format

public static final Configuration.Config transcoded_audio_format
The audio format (container) used for the transcoded files.
The default is wav.
See The JAVE (Java Audio Video Encoder) library web site.

transcoded_audio_number_of_channels

public static final Configuration.Config transcoded_audio_number_of_channels
The number of channels in the transcoded audio files. If the source is mono and the number of channels is 2 a file with two identical channels is created. If the source is stereo and the number of channels is 1 the two channels are down mixed.
The default is mono so 1 channel.
